    vellum_post_150.body = u'In the damper months, I like to throw a small stove in my pack. A warm cup of tea encourages further exploration of the woods, which seem to come alive after a rain.\n\n<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/pigmonkey/2877399740/" title="Cedar Tea by Pig Monkey, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3027/2877399740_8a09201056.jpg" width="500" height="375" alt="Cedar Tea" /></a>\n\n<blockquote>We do not go to the green woods and crystal waters to rough it, we go to smooth it. We get it rough enough at home; in towns and cities; in shops, offices, stores, banks anywhere that we may be placed -- with the necessity always present of being on time and up to our work; of providing for the dependent ones; of keeping up, catching up, or getting left.. "Alas for the life-long battle, whose bravest slogan is bread."\n\n-Nessmuk, Woodcraft and Camping</blockquote>\n\n<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/pigmonkey/2876567833/" title="Cedar Tea by Pig Monkey, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2233/2876567833_b0bae706f4.jpg" width="500" height="375" alt="Cedar Tea" /></a>'
    vellum_post_150.body_rendered = u'<p>In the damper months, I like to throw a small stove in my pack. A warm cup of tea encourages further exploration of the woods, which seem to come alive after a rain.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/pigmonkey/2877399740/" title="Cedar Tea by Pig Monkey, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3027/2877399740_8a09201056.jpg" width="500" height="375" alt="Cedar Tea" /></a>\n<blockquote>We do not go to the green woods and crystal waters to rough it, we go to smooth it. We get it rough enough at home; in towns and cities; in shops, offices, stores, banks anywhere that we may be placed &#8212; with the necessity always present of being on time and up to our work; of providing for the dependent ones; of keeping up, catching up, or getting left.. &#8220;Alas for the life-long battle, whose bravest slogan is bread.&#8221;</p>\n<p>-Nessmuk, Woodcraft and Camping</blockquote>\n<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/pigmonkey/2876567833/" title="Cedar Tea by Pig Monkey, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2233/2876567833_b0bae706f4.jpg" width="500" height="375" alt="Cedar Tea" /></a></p>'
