    vellum_post_262.body = u'Greetings from Portland. (Surprise?)\n\nI\'m staying in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hawthorne,_Portland,_Oregon" >Hawthorne District</a>, which so far seems to be an over-sized <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capitol_Hill,_Seattle,_Washington" >Capitol Hill</a> -- same shops, even.\n\nIf anyone has suggestions for that which must be done or seen, let me know. I head home Friday.\n\n<a href="http://trimet.org/" >Public transportation</a> here seems to be overpriced, but I can rent a bike for $15, so I think I might do that tomorrow. Walking around today, it looked this area was bike-friendly, but the other side of the Willamette River... not so much.'
    vellum_post_262.body_rendered = u'<p>Greetings from Portland. (Surprise?)</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m staying in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hawthorne,_Portland,_Oregon">Hawthorne District</a>, which so far seems to be an over-sized <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capitol_Hill,_Seattle,_Washington">Capitol Hill</a> &#8212; same shops, even.</p>\n<p>If anyone has suggestions for that which must be done or seen, let me know. I head home Friday.</p>\n<p><a href="http://trimet.org/">Public transportation</a> here seems to be overpriced, but I can rent a bike for $15, so I think I might do that tomorrow. Walking around today, it looked this area was bike-friendly, but the other side of the Willamette River&#8230; not so much.</p>'
