    vellum_post_453.body = u"If there's one thing college has done for me, it's to reinforce the notion that a piece of paper with an accomplishment written on it means little. A title such as Dr. and a jumble of letters after someone's name is not, by any means, a measure of intelligence.\n\nAt the end of each term, we'd fill out evaluations for our classes and Professors -- but there was never a question as to if the Professor had a grasp of the subject they were lecturing on or not. Why is that?\nDangerous assumptions, says I."
    vellum_post_453.body_rendered = u'<p>If there&#8217;s one thing college has done for me, it&#8217;s to reinforce the notion that a piece of paper with an accomplishment written on it means little. A title such as Dr. and a jumble of letters after someone&#8217;s name is not, by any means, a measure of intelligence.</p>\n<p>At the end of each term, we&#8217;d fill out evaluations for our classes and Professors &#8212; but there was never a question as to if the Professor had a grasp of the subject they were lecturing on or not. Why is that?\nDangerous assumptions, says I.</p>'
