    vellum_post_697 = Post()
    vellum_post_697.title = u"When CUPS won't die..."
    vellum_post_697.slug = u'when-cups-is-a-bitch'
    vellum_post_697.author = None
    vellum_post_697.markup = u'markdown'
    vellum_post_697.body = u"I upgraded CUPS yesterday and apparently broke my printing. After some googling and searching on the Gentoo forums, I came up with the following:\n1) Delete the printer from http://localhost:631/printers/\n2) <i>killall cupsd</i> (perhaps using the PID and -9 switch if the bastard won't die)\n3) <i>/etc/init.d/cupsd zap</i>\n4) <i>/etc/init.d/cupsd start</i>\n5) Add the printer back into the web panel\n\nIt works now.\n\n(Note that you could probably fix the problem with a reboot, but that's just so Windows-like.)"
    vellum_post_697.body_rendered = u'<p>I upgraded CUPS yesterday and apparently broke my printing. After some googling and searching on the Gentoo forums, I came up with the following:\n1) Delete the printer from http://localhost:631/printers/\n2) <i>killall cupsd</i> (perhaps using the PID and -9 switch if the bastard won&#8217;t die)\n3) <i>/etc/init.d/cupsd zap</i>\n4) <i>/etc/init.d/cupsd start</i>\n5) Add the printer back into the web panel</p>\n<p>It works now.</p>\n<p>(Note that you could probably fix the problem with a reboot, but that&#8217;s just so Windows-like.)</p>'
