    vellum_post_816 = Post()
    vellum_post_816.title = u'More Crypto and Mldonkey'
    vellum_post_816.slug = u'more-crypto-and-mldonkey'
    vellum_post_816.author = None
    vellum_post_816.markup = u'markdown'
    vellum_post_816.body = u'I finished <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/tg/detail/-/0140244328/qid=1058636279/sr=8-1/ref=sr_8_1/104-7034097-1687116?v=glance&s=books&n=507846" >Crypto</a> a few days ago. It\'s more of a recent history of cryptography (Lucifer/DES, public key, RSA, PGP) but the author loves to focus on how much the NSA tried to fsck everything up. Ok book, I guess.<br />\n<br />\nI\'ve recently discovered <a href="http://savannah.nongnu.org/projects/mldonkey/" >MlDonkey</a>: an open-source p2p client that connects to the Donkey (edonkey, emule), Fasttrack (Kazzaa), IRC Direct Connect, Soulseek, BitTorrent, Gnutella, and Open Napster networks. An excellent idea but it can\'t seem to keep a connection to the servers so it takes a long time to download anything. A project to watch, though.'
    vellum_post_816.body_rendered = u'<p>I finished <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/tg/detail/-/0140244328/qid=1058636279/sr=8-1/ref=sr_8_1/104-7034097-1687116?v=glance&amp;s=books&amp;n=507846">Crypto</a> a few days ago. It&#8217;s more of a recent history of cryptography (Lucifer/DES, public key, RSA, PGP) but the author loves to focus on how much the NSA tried to fsck everything up. Ok book, I guess.<br />\n<br />\nI&#8217;ve recently discovered <a href="http://savannah.nongnu.org/projects/mldonkey/">MlDonkey</a>: an open-source p2p client that connects to the Donkey (edonkey, emule), Fasttrack (Kazzaa), IRC Direct Connect, Soulseek, BitTorrent, Gnutella, and Open Napster networks. An excellent idea but it can&#8217;t seem to keep a connection to the servers so it takes a long time to download anything. A project to watch, though.</p>'
